{{Infobox person | name= Tengku Rethwan | birth_name= Tengku Rethwan bin Tengku Mansor | image = Tengku Rethwan Tengku Mansor.jpg | caption = Tengku Rethwan Tengku Mansor is the Chairman of President College. | image_size= | birth_date= {{Birth date and age|1954|11|4}} | birth_place= [[Kelana Jaya]], [[Selangor]], [[Malaysia]] | residence= | other_names= | education= | alma_mater= | occupation= | known_for= | notable_works= | style= | spouse= | awards= }}
[[Malay titles|Datuk]] [[Dr.]]'''Tengku Rethwan bin Tengku Mansor''' is a prominent Malaysian businessman who ventured into [[Selangor]] state politics.<ref>Business News.[http://biz.thestar.com.my/marketwatch/schangecode.asp?searchstr=0087 "Recent Change of Share Holdings Announcements"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131019054623/http://biz.thestar.com.my/marketwatch/schangecode.asp?searchstr=0087 |date=2013-10-19 }}, ''[[The Star (Malaysia)|The Star]]'', Kuala Lumpur, 12 August 2008. Retrieved on 17 April 2013.</ref> Tengku Rethwan is the chairman of President college. He is one of the [[Barisan Nasional]] candidates for GE-13.<ref>Teh Eng Hock. [http://thestar.com.my/news/story.asp?file=/2013/4/16/nation/20130416142545&sec=nation "GE13: Selangor - Perkasa's Zulkifli to contest in Shah Alam as 'friend of BN'"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130512170201/http://thestar.com.my/news/story.asp?file=%2F2013%2F4%2F16%2Fnation%2F20130416142545&sec=nation |date=2013-05-12 }}, ''[[The Star (Malaysia)|The Star]]'', Shah Alam, 16 April 2013. Retrieved on 17 April 2013.</ref>
==Education== Tengku Rethwan started his tertiary education in UiTM and graduated with Diploma in Science in 1975. He then later obtained his MBBS from [[University Malaya]], Bachelor of Law (LLB-London) and currently he is pursuing his PHD on Social Networking in Entrepreneurship at the University of Amsterdam.<ref>http://www.uva.nl/en/home</ref>
==Knighthood== Tengku Rethwan was awarded the Darjah Paduka Tuanku Jaafar [DPTJ], Negeri Sembilan in the year 2000 which carries the title Datuk.<ref>http://www.royalark.net/Malaysia/negri8.htm</ref>
==President College Chairman== As the Chairman of President College Kuala Lumpur, Tengku Rethwan believes that education lies in the development of industry driven knowledge, practical skills and character development. He is also the founder of the college.<ref>Message from Principal.[http://www.president.edu.my/about-us/message-from-principal.html "President College"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121116152055/http://www.president.edu.my/about-us/message-from-principal.html |date=2012-11-16 }}, ''[[President College]]'', Kuala Lumpur.</ref>
